cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: The paper deals with information theoretic concepts such as secrecy sum-rate, power control, and channel state information. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also deals with security and privacy, which suggests the sub-category cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of cooperative jamming and power control suggests the sub-categories cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the use of fading channels suggests the sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia).
